HEADWORD: Peloria
<hw>Pe*lo"ri*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., from Gr.
<?/ monstrous.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Abnormal regularity; the
state of certain flowers, which, being naturally irregular, have become
regular through a symmetrical repetition of the special
irregularity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

